  <metadata>
    <id>mousewithoutborders</id>
    <version>2.1.2.4</version>
    <title>Mouse Without Borders</title>
    <authors>Microsoft Garage,Truong Do</authors>
    <owners>Anthony Mastrean</owners>
    <projectUrl>https://getsatisfaction.com/mouse_without_borders</projectUrl>
    <iconUrl>https://github.com/AnthonyMastrean/nugetpackages/raw/mousewithoutborders/mousewithoutborders/mousewithoutborders.ico</iconUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <description>Mouse Without Borders is a project that allows you to reach across your PC's as if they were part of one single desktop. You can move files between the 2 computers simply by dragging them from one desktop to another. In fact you can control up to four computers from a single mouse and keyboard with no extra hardware needed.</description>
    <summary>Mouse Without Borders is a project that allows you to reach across your PC's as if they were part of one single desktop.</summary>
    <releaseNotes>
v2.1.2.0801
* Add an option to allow user to go through the setup experience again

v2.1.2.0704
* Add a mini SnagIt feature where you can capture an area on the screen of any machine then paste to any machine in the matrix. The default hotkey to use this new feature is Ctrl+Shift+S.

v2.1.2.0627
* Mini log: Gives user an easy way to generate short log for a quick triage

v2.1.2.0616 
* Fix: Shared clipboard does not work for some users.
* Personalize Lock Screen for Windows 8.
* Keyboard Layout Mappings.

v2.1.2.0525
* Fix "Alt+Tab not working in Win8 RP".
* Run on Windows Phone 7, you can now use your phone as a wireless mouse/keyboard!
* Option to draw mouse cursor in Windows 8 tablet.
* Option to hit Ctrl-Alt-L twice to lock all machines.
* Per machine installation, desktop shortcut created for all users.
* Bind to network adapter instead of IP Address.
* Bug fix: Mouse jumps to center screen when hitting 'L'.
* Bug fix: When a machine is behind a different router, keyboard/mouse only works one direction.
* CAD simulation (Win7/SeverR2)
* Improved UI for two-row machine matrix.
* Compatible with .Net 4.0, MM runs on .Net 4 when it is available in the machine. Win8 users do not have to enable .Net 2.0.
* Bug fix: Mouse speed differs in X and Y directions with a remote machine having multiple monitors or different screen orientation.
* Hotkey to toggle Easy mouse. User can hold Ctrl key and move mouse to switch to other machines when Easy Mouse is disabled.
* Option to center mouse cursor when switching machine.
* Support logging
    </releaseNotes>
    <tags>microsoft garage mouse monitor</tags>
  </metadata>
